                "href": "/profile/Shruti-Paranjape"
            },
            "answer_text": "Here's how :1. Download Audacity (It's free! Woohoo!)2. Open the song on Audacity3. Select \"Split stereo track\" on the drop-down menu of the song.4. Select any one of the tracks and then select \"Invert\" under the \"Effects\" menu.5. Put both tracks on \"Mono\" mode on the drop-down menu of each track.6. Select \"Make stereo track\" on the drop-down menu of any one of the tracks.7. Go to the \"File\" menu and \"Export file\" to save as an mp3 or any other kind of supported format. This will work only with mp3 with a certain kind of recording. For a distorted sounding karaoke version of the song, you can try using the GuitarPro tab and singing along. ",
